      "content": "The problem is, a \"test batch\" won't satisfy the board if the results look messy. Our clients pay us specifically because we provide a certain type of candidate that is proven to succeed in these high-pressure environments. There's a reason why the current pipeline looks the way it does—it matches the existing power structures of these firms. If you start pulling from \"non-traditional\" backgrounds just to tick a box, you're going to end up sending people who don't \"fit\" the culture, and that's going to damage our reputation. Honestly, the board is leaning towards thinking your logic is fundamentally flawed because it's tied to these specific demographics. Are you sure you aren't just going to trade performance for optics?",
